FOOT-AND-MOUTH DISEASE, SUSPECTED - ARGENTINA: NOT
***********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
<http://www.fas.org/promed/ahead>
See Also
Foot & mouth disease, suspected - Argentina (Buenos Aires) 990108134903
Date: Tue, 12 Jan 1999 11:36:33 -0300
From: "SENASA - Rel. Internacionales relint@inea.com.ar" <relint@inea.com.ar>

The NATIONAL SERVICE OF AGRIFOOD HEALTH AND QUALITY (SENASA) of
ARGENTINA in the framework of the 1998-2000 Footh and Mouth Disease
Program and in accordance with the rules stablished in the
Presidential Decree No1324, which prohibit the vaccination against
Foot and Mouth Disease in all the country, inform that in December of
1998 a SIMULATION of foot and mouth disease outbreak in the Brandsen
city, Buenos Aires Province.
**********************
Argentina has no more outbreaks since April 1994 and at 30 April
1999 we expect to leave the vaccination.
**********************

This comunication had been send to OIE, MERCOSUR countries, Chile,
INPPAZ, USA, JAPAN, UE. In this case, we would like if you can clear
up as soon as possible, because your information is causing serious
problem.
--
Lic. Gustavo Idigoras
Chairman of SENASA Bureau of International Affairs
Ministerio de Economia y Obras y Servicios Publicos
Secretaria de Agricultura, Ganaderia, Pesca y Alimentacion
Servicio Nacional de Sanidad y Calidad Agroalimentaria
Coordinacion de Relaciones Internacionales e Institucionales
Av. Paseo Colon 367 (1063) Buenos Aires, ARGENTINA
phone/fax 334-4738
<relint@inea.com.ar>
--------------------------
Original text:
El SERVICIO NACIONAL DE SANIDAD Y CALIDAD AGROALIMENTARIA (SENASA),
en el marco del Programa de Erradicacion de la Fiebre Aftosa
1998-2000 y en cumplimiento de las pautas establecidas con vistas al
cumplimiento del Decreto del Poder Ejecutivo Nacional N 1324, por el
que se prohibe la vacunacion contra la Fiebre Aftosa en todo el
Territorio Nacional, informa que en el mes de diciembre de 1998 se
realizo un SIMULACRO de aparicion de un foco de Fiebre Aftosa en la
localidad de de Brandsen, Provincia de Buenos Aires.
-----------------------
*********We apologise for our misreading of the original simulation
report, and sincerely regret the trouble this has caused the Argentinian
department of agriculture.
--
Dr Jack Woodall
Director, ProMED-mail
Institute of Biomedical Sciences
Federal University of Rio de Janeiro
Rio de Janeiro - RJ, Brazil
<woodall@bioqmed.ufrj.br>
